graph TB
    subgraph "rhbk-demo namespace"
        CLIENT[jwt-test-client Pod]
        KC[Keycloak]
        PG[(PostgreSQL)]
    end

    subgraph "zero-trust-workload-identity-manager namespace"
        SERVER[SPIRE Server<br/>Trust Bundle]
        OIDC[SPIRE OIDC<br/>Discovery Provider]
    end

    subgraph "External Access"
        ROUTE[OpenShift Route<br/>keycloak-rhbk-demo.apps...]
    end

    CLIENT -->|Step 2: POST Token Endpoint<br/>with JWT-SVID| ROUTE
    ROUTE --> KC

    KC -->|Step 3a: Extract sub<br/>from JWT-SVID| KC
    KC -->|Step 3b: Find Client<br/>by sub claim| PG
    PG -.Client Config.-> KC

    KC -->|Step 3c: Get SPIFFE IdP<br/>by issuer| PG
    PG -.SPIFFE IdP Config.-> KC

    KC -->|Step 3d: GET /.well-known/<br/>openid-configuration| OIDC
    OIDC -.JWKS URI.-> KC

    KC -->|Step 3e: GET /keys<br/>Fetch JWKS| OIDC
    OIDC -->|Request Bundle| SERVER
    SERVER -.Public Keys.-> OIDC
    OIDC -.JWKS<br/>Public Keys.-> KC

    KC -->|Step 3f: Verify JWT-SVID<br/>Signature with JWKS| KC
    KC -->|Step 3g: Validate Claims<br/>sub, iss, aud, exp| KC

    KC -->|Step 4a: Authentication<br/>Successful| KC
    KC -->|Step 4b: Generate<br/>Access Token| KC
    KC -->|Step 4c: HTTP 200 OK<br/>Return Access Token| ROUTE
    ROUTE --> CLIENT

    Note1[Authentication Complete<br/>Client can now use Access Token<br/>to access protected resources]
    CLIENT -.success.-> Note1

    classDef client fill:#ff6d00,stroke:#fff,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    classDef keycloak fill:#008aaa,stroke:#fff,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    classDef spire fill:#00c853,stroke:#fff,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    classDef db fill:#4285f4,stroke:#fff,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    classDef route fill:#f57c00,stroke:#fff,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    classDef note fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f57f17,stroke-width:2px,color:#000

    class CLIENT client
    class KC keycloak
    class SERVER,OIDC spire
    class PG db
    class ROUTE route
    class Note1 note
